--- PostgreSQL Database Configuration ---
WARNING: Use strong, unique passwords in production.
POSTGRES_DB=campus_db
POSTGRES_USER=admin
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=supersecretpassword

--- Flask & SQLAlchemy Configuration ---
This URL is used by the backend service to connect to the 'db' service container.
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://admin:supersecretpassword@db:5432/campus_db

Generate a long, random string for the secret key.
You can use: python -c 'import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(24))'
SECRET_KEY=your_super_secret_flask_key

--- Celery & Redis Configuration ---
These URLs are used by the backend and worker services to connect to the 'redis' service container.
CELERY_BROKER_URL=redis://redis:6379/0
CELERY_RESULT_BACKEND=redis://redis:6379/0

--- React Frontend Configuration ---
The base URL for the backend API that the React app will call.
This should match the host and port where your backend is exposed.
REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:5000/api